From 5d1837a22f0f2d89925d12ce045a21f04607a866 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Robin Jarry <robin@jarry.cc>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026 19:09:59 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] api: add metadata field to series model

Add a JSONField to Series for storing arbitrary key-value metadata.
This allows external integrations (e.g. forge bridges) to associate
their own references with patchwork series, such as mapping a series
to a GitHub pull request.

The field is exposed in API v1.5 and is writable by project
maintainers. SeriesDetail is changed from RetrieveAPIView to
RetrieveUpdateAPIView to support PATCH/PUT requests.

Signed-off-by: Robin Jarry <robin@jarry.cc>
---
 patchwork/api/series.py                      | 17 +++++++--
 patchwork/migrations/0050_series_metadata.py | 21 +++++++++++
 patchwork/models.py                          | 10 ++++++
 patchwork/tests/api/test_series.py           | 38 +++++++++++++++++---
 4 files changed, 78 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 patchwork/migrations/0050_series_metadata.py

